  "body": "# Problem\nThe user is not informed of the moment the keys have successfully been generated and moved to the Keycard. This could lead to an undesirable situation when the user:\n\n- Cancels the process when asked to write down the PUK code and Pairing code\n- Generates new keys\n- Tries to store these Keys on Keycard\n\nThe user will currently receive the following message and will no longer be able to use the card. However the user will not be able to login or recover the existing account (they will not have written down their seed phrase at this stage)\n\n![photo_2020-02-10_16 34 19_1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35233054/74230779-5cf43d00-4cc5-11ea-8af1-0d0d163a4bdc.jpeg)\n\n## Implementation\nShow a state that the keys have been generated and placed on the Keycard to better inform the user that at this point they can longer return.\n\nIn addition, solutions depend on:\n\n- Can the card hold multiple multiaccounts? (Why not?)\n- Can the back up seed phrase step precede the PUK and Pairing code? (At least that way, the keys can be accessed)\n- Can the multiaccount be added to `Your keys`, without the PUK and Pairing code been written down, for a limited time. With the passcode providing access. Blocking all functionality, only showing the PUK code and Pairing code\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n## Notes\nNeeds specification of options\n\n## Future Steps\n- Design screens for decided upon option\n- Implementation",
